Boil a large #pot{} of water. Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{4} (or use a
#garlic press{} if you have one). Cut the @green chilli{1} in half lengthways,
remove the seeds and finely chop both this and the @chives{1}(chopped).
Finally, roughly chop the @Serrano ham{1} and the @tiger prawns{250}.

> It's even quicker to cut the serrano ham and chives with sharp scissors.

Once the water has come to the boil, add the @linguine{400} together with the
@vegetable stock pot{1}.

> Make sure you keep this stock, as we'll use it for the sauce later.

Cook it for around ~{10%minutes} or until it is 'al dente'.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of
> firmness left in the middle.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Cook your
chilli, serrano ham and prawns for ~{2%minutes}. Season with a good pinch of
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> White pepper is best but black is just fine.

When your prawns have just turned pink, add your garlic. Continue to cook for
~{1%minute} before adding in a good glug of the stock from your pasta pot.
Turn the heat to low and add the @crème fraîche{1} and three quarters of your
chives. Let your sauce simmer for a few mins until it goes nice and velvety.

> If the sauce still seems too thick, add another splash of stock water.

Drain your pasta and add it to your sauce. Cut the @lemon{1} in half and squeeze
over a good splash of lemon juice. Add a little more salt and pepper if
necessary. Toss the pan (or gently stir with a #wooden spoon{}) to combine all
of your ingredients.

Serve with a sprinkle of your remaining chives and tuck in.